  "notes": "Franco-Provençal / Arpitan. A distinct Gallo-Romance language intermediate between French (Oïl) and Occitan (Oc). Spoken historically in Savoie, Lyonnais, Suisse Romande, and Aosta Valley. Key features: (1) CA- → [tʃ] (like French, vs Occitan [ka]). (2) Final -a preserved (unlike French). (3) /u/→/y/ fronting (shared with French). (4) Less nasal vowels than French. ~150,000 speakers, severely endangered (Kristol 2016).",
